{"id":34941,"title":"Tailored strategies for staged management of complex congenital cardiac lesions.","abstract":"Although many complex congenital cardiac lesions can be primarily repaired, there remain circumstances where a staged approach may carry lower risk than a primary repair. We present 4 clinical cases where stable intermediate stages allowed somatic growth and facilitated successful biventricular repair or univentricular palliation. ","date":"2014-04-03","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24694425","annotations":[{"name":"Heart","weight":0.775211,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart"},{"name":"Palliative care","weight":0.659725,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palliative_care"},{"name":"Congenital disorder","weight":0.480865,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_disorder"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.403857,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Risk","weight":0.289795,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"},{"name":"Somatic","weight":0.0256641,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somatic"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.0250212,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"},{"name":"Coordination complex","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coordination_complex"},{"name":"Strategy","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strategy"},{"name":"Stable","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stable"},{"name":"Secondary education","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secondary_education"},{"name":"Primary education","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primar